## ETAPA 2 — Migrar storage para Cloudflare R2

**Por que R2:** S3-compatible, 10GB grátis, barato depois disso (~$0.015/GB).
Necessário antes de ir para Vercel ou qualquer plataforma serverless.

### 2.1 Criar bucket R2 no Cloudflare

1. Acessar https://dash.cloudflare.com → R2
2. Criar bucket: `subtitlestudio-media`
3. Gerar API token com permissão de leitura/escrita no bucket
4. Anotar: `Account ID`, `Access Key ID`, `Secret Access Key`, `Bucket Name`

### 2.2 Instalar SDK

```bash
cd web
npm install @aws-sdk/client-s3 @aws-sdk/s3-request-presigner
```

### 2.3 Criar serviço de storage abstrato

**Arquivo:** `web/src/server/storage/storage.service.ts`

```ts
// Interface que tanto o storage local quanto o R2 implementam
export interface StorageService {
  save(key: string, buffer: Buffer, mimeType: string): Promise<void>;
  getUrl(key: string): Promise<string>;
  delete(key: string): Promise<void>;
  getStream(key: string): Promise<NodeJS.ReadableStream>;
}
```

**Arquivo:** `web/src/server/storage/r2-storage.service.ts`

```ts
import {
  S3Client,
  PutObjectCommand,
  GetObjectCommand,
  DeleteObjectCommand,
} from "@aws-sdk/client-s3";
import { getSignedUrl } from "@aws-sdk/s3-request-presigner";

const client = new S3Client({
  region: "auto",
  endpoint: `https://${process.env.R2_ACCOUNT_ID}.r2.cloudflarestorage.com`,
  credentials: {
    accessKeyId: process.env.R2_ACCESS_KEY_ID!,
    secretAccessKey: process.env.R2_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY!,
  },
});

export const r2Storage = {
  async save(key: string, buffer: Buffer, mimeType: string) {
    await client.send(
      new PutObjectCommand({
        Bucket: process.env.R2_BUCKET_NAME!,
        Key: key,
        Body: buffer,
        ContentType: mimeType,
      }),
    );
  },

  async getSignedUrl(key: string, expiresIn = 3600) {
    return getSignedUrl(
      client,
      new GetObjectCommand({
        Bucket: process.env.R2_BUCKET_NAME!,
        Key: key,
      }),
      { expiresIn },
    );
  },

  async delete(key: string) {
    await client.send(
      new DeleteObjectCommand({
        Bucket: process.env.R2_BUCKET_NAME!,
        Key: key,
      }),
    );
  },
};
```

### 2.4 Variáveis de ambiente para R2

Adicionar em `.env` e no Railway:

```env
R2_ACCOUNT_ID=seu-account-id
R2_ACCESS_KEY_ID=sua-access-key
R2_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=sua-secret-key
R2_BUCKET_NAME=subtitlestudio-media
```

### 2.5 Migrar MediaStorageService para usar R2

Em `web/src/server/transcription/media-storage.service.ts`,
substituir as operações de `fs` por chamadas ao `r2Storage`:

- `fs.writeFile(path, buffer)` → `r2Storage.save(key, buffer, mimeType)`
- `path.join(dir, key)` → `r2Storage.getSignedUrl(key)`
- `fs.unlink(path)` → `r2Storage.delete(key)`

### 2.6 Verificar

- [ ] Upload de áudio salva no R2 (verificar no dashboard Cloudflare)
- [ ] Transcrição consegue ler o arquivo do R2
- [ ] Download do ZIP funciona
- [ ] Arquivo antigo no disco pode ser deletado

